-- Mori Seiki to Pay $120 Million for More of Gildemeister, Nikkei Reports
-- B y   P e t e r   J .   B r e n n a n
-- 2010-11-16T17:22:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/mori-seiki-to-pay-120-million-for-more-of-gildemeister-nikkei-reports.html
Mori Seiki Co. plans to increase its
stake in the German firm Gildemeister AG to more than 20 percent
from 5 percent, Nikkei English News reported, without saying
where it obtained the information.   Mori Seiki will purchase more then 10 billion yen ($119.9
million) of Gildemeister shares and convert the German firm into
an equity-method affiliate, Nikkei said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter J. Brennan at 
 pbrennan3@bloomberg.net  